{{see|Tinker}}
==English==
===Noun===
'''tinker'''
# an [[itinerant]] tinsmith and [[mender]] of [[household]] [[utensil]]s made of tin
#(''mostly British, Irish'') A member of the [[travelling]] community. A [[gypsy]]. 
:The term is not common now, and was considered offensive.

===Verb===
'''to tinker'''  (''intransitive'' or ''transitive'')

# to [[fiddle]] with something in an [[attempt]] to [[fix]], [[mend]] or [[improve]] it, especially in an [[experimental]] or [[unskilled]] manner
# to work as a tinker

